<p>I have a <code>Home</code>. Each <code>Home</code> has a list of <code>Room</code>s. Each <code>Room</code> has zero or more <code>Person</code>s.</p>  <p>I would like to count total persons of each home. But I can't add a new variable to record person count in any backing beans or entity. So I'd like to count it in the view only via <code>&lt;c:set&gt;</code>.</p>  <p>My first attempt look like:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;c:set var="personCount" value="${0}" /&gt; &lt;ui:repeat var="home" value="#{mybackingBean.homes}"&gt;     &lt;ui:repeat var="room" value="#{home.rooms}"&gt;         ${personCount += room.persons.size()}     &lt;/ui:repeat&gt;     &lt;h:panelGrid columns="2"&gt;         &lt;h:outputLabel value="#{home.id}" /&gt;         &lt;h:outputLabel value="#{personCount}" /&gt;     &lt;/h:panelGrid&gt; &lt;/ui:repeat&gt; </code></pre>  <p>How can I achieve it?</p>